{
  "stem": "8.3",
  "chunk_idx": 10,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 8.1,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "And by this time, I had so much anger in me.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "This was probably the only time that I expressed that anger.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "I went into that house with an ax, and I broke the piano and furniture and the Dutch masters on the wall.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "Whatever I could, I destroyed.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "Now, many people went into homes to rob.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "I did not want anything, except for three things that I took from the house.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "I took a white tablecloth.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "I took an apron.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "And I took a little silver cup that I still have that had the initials EF on it.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "And I decided that I would pretend that that belonged to my grandfather who's name was Engel Farkas.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "And I took that with me, and I kept it.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 22,
      "text": "And I really didn't understand.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 23,
      "text": "I was 16 by now, but I didn't understand that this was-- that I longed to establish normal life again, and these were the symbols of my home-- a white tablecloth, an apron, and a [NON-ENGLISH].",
      "word_count": 36
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 24,
      "text": "[SIGHS]",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yes, this was in Langenbielau.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yes.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And as I said, there were people in the town around me, but I didn't see the people around me.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And then we decided that we had to have-- they said in order to leave town-- you can't just leave town-- you had to have some kind of paper, some kind of a document.",
      "word_count": 34
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "So I went into another city, which was Peterswaldau, which was nearby-- I don't know how I got there, whether we walked there or some-- and asked them to give us some kind of a document so we would go home.",
      "word_count": 41
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "But there was no way to go home.",
      "word_count": 8
    }
  ],
